50|$|Auto-enucleation (<b>oedipism)</b> {{and other}} forms of serious self-inflicted eye injury are an {{extremely}} rare form of severe self-harm that usually results from mental illnesses involving acute psychosis. The name comes from Oedipus of Greek mythology, who gouged out his own eyes.|$|E
